00:23:40,000 --> 00:23:41,840
We had no idea if you were Black or white.

557
00:23:41,850 --> 00:23:43,060
Step out of the car.

558
00:23:43,490 --> 00:23:44,870
Look, I'm police.

559
00:23:45,180 --> 00:23:48,530
My name's Kevin Atwater, badge number 52784.

560
00:23:48,530 --> 00:23:49,820
I work with the intelligence unit.

561
00:23:49,820 --> 00:23:51,020
Y'all can check whatever you want.

562
00:23:51,020 --> 00:23:52,870
I said, step out of the vehicle.

563
00:23:54,170 --> 00:23:56,310
Nah, I'm not stepping out of no damn vehicle,

564
00:23:56,740 --> 00:23:59,450
but I will show you my badge nice and slow.

565
00:23:59,450 --> 00:24:00,860
Okay, so y'all can--

566
00:24:09,650 --> 00:24:12,020
Okay, look, fellas, I'm stepping out of the car.

567
00:24:14,480 --> 00:24:15,560
Shut the door.

568
00:24:15,640 --> 00:24:17,860
I'm shutting the door. My hands are high.

569
00:24:20,300 --> 00:24:22,060
You see my star and my gun.

570
00:24:22,500 --> 00:24:24,860
If you look in my left pocket, you'll find my ID.

571
00:24:31,210 --> 00:24:32,410
He's telling the truth.

572
00:24:32,670 --> 00:24:33,870
He's the police, Ron.

573
00:24:36,760 --> 00:24:38,150
So what you a cop?

574
00:24:38,360 --> 00:24:39,280
I got an anonymous tip

575
00:24:39,280 --> 00:24:40,740
that a guy was selling drugs in this car.

576
00:24:40,740 --> 00:24:41,690
What are you talking about?

577
00:24:41,690 --> 00:24:45,290
The guy sold a kilo of heroin to a dirty cop in a blue Dodge.

578
00:24:46,690 --> 00:24:48,100
You with Nolan's crew?

579
00:24:51,880 --> 00:24:54,790
Well, search the car, Ron. Look wherever you want,

580
00:24:54,790 --> 00:24:56,060
but you ain't gonna find a damn thing

581
00:24:56,060 --> 00:24:57,670
'cause I already found the dope.

582
00:24:58,410 --> 00:24:59,610
It was in the trunk.

583
00:25:02,590 --> 00:25:04,360
Is this really what you wanna do,

584
00:25:04,510 --> 00:25:05,560
Black man?

585
00:25:22,770 --> 00:25:23,600
You wanted to see me?

586
00:25:24,160 --> 00:25:25,030
Yeah.

587
00:25:25,810 --> 00:25:26,970
Shut the door.

588
00:25:31,580 --> 00:25:33,450
So I heard you got into a beef last night

589
00:25:33,450 --> 00:25:35,430
with a couple patrol officers.

590
00:25:35,430 --> 00:25:36,600
More complicated than that.

591
00:25:36,600 --> 00:25:37,940
I'm sure it is.

592
00:25:39,040 --> 00:25:41,330
One of Nolan's boys pulled me over last night

593
00:25:41,700 --> 00:25:43,620
hoping to find dope in my car.

594
00:25:45,010 --> 00:25:45,910
Dope?

595
00:25:46,010 --> 00:25:48,150
They planted a kilo of heroin in my car.

596
00:25:48,760 --> 00:25:50,340
Why didn't you tell me?

597
00:25:50,750 --> 00:25:52,410
Didn't want to get you involved.

598
00:25:53,400 --> 00:25:54,360
Okay.

599
00:25:55,960 --> 00:25:57,520
So tell me, what's your plan?

600
00:25:58,840 --> 00:26:00,110
Going to IED?

601
00:26:01,550 --> 00:26:03,420
I can't prove they planted the dope

602
00:26:04,080 --> 00:26:05,810
or that they're even harassing me.

603
00:26:06,610 --> 00:26:08,720
So I'll just sit back and wait for one of these punks

604
00:26:08,720 --> 00:26:11,310
to screw up and leave behind some actual evidence.

605
00:26:12,200 --> 00:26:13,870
Don't really have any other options.

606
00:26:13,870 --> 00:26:14,910
Sure you do.

607
00:26:19,170 --> 00:26:20,280
Kevin...

608
00:26:23,330 --> 00:26:25,720
The blue wall is a tricky thing.

609
00:26:26,640 --> 00:26:29,690
It's not a person or an object. It's a code.

610
00:26:30,590 --> 00:26:32,230
You never really see it.

611
00:26:34,630 --> 00:26:36,880
I mean, it's there, but it's not there.

612
00:26:37,140 --> 00:26:38,140
You understand?

613
00:26:40,950 --> 00:26:44,470
It's like trying to fight a ghost, Kevin.

614
00:26:48,140 --> 00:26:49,490
I know, Sarge.

615
00:26:53,190 --> 00:26:54,860
I just wanna do this my way.

616
00:27:04,400 --> 00:27:07,080
Okay, so where we at with Anna Salgado?

617
00:27:07,080 --> 00:27:09,640
Not sure--I'm meeting up with Ruzek right now

618
00:27:09,640 --> 00:27:11,100
to check out surveillance video.

619
00:27:11,960 --> 00:27:12,950
Hit it.

620
00:27:22,420 --> 00:27:23,930
You know these guys are pushing their luck.

621
00:27:23,930 --> 00:27:25,720
- They need to know that. - I told you, I'm good.

622
00:27:25,720 --> 00:27:27,070
- No. - It's over.

623
00:27:27,570 --> 00:27:28,990
Are you gonna talk to this punk Gaffney,

624
00:27:28,990 --> 00:27:30,660
or am I gonna talk to him, seriously?

625
00:27:31,540 --> 00:27:32,500
Check it out.

626
00:27:37,180 --> 00:27:39,510
All right, well, let's run it through facial rec.

627
00:27:40,840 --> 00:27:42,480
Miguel Cortez, he's a career punk.

628
00:27:42,480 --> 00:27:44,480
He's got five priors, two armed robberies,

629
00:27:44,480 --> 00:27:46,090
two ag bats, one attempted murder,

630
00:27:46,090 --> 00:27:47,610
six or seven drug charges.

631
00:27:47,730 --> 00:27:48,770
- Hailey... - Yeah.

632
00:27:48,770 --> 00:27:51,070
Pull up the surveillance video from the church.

633
00:27:53,490 --> 00:27:54,450
Okay.

634
00:27:55,210 --> 00:27:56,510
Is that Miguel?

635
00:27:57,120 --> 00:27:59,050
Looks like him. Same height, same build.

636
00:27:59,050 --> 00:28:01,190
- It's just not clear enough. - Yeah, but come on.

637
00:28:01,190 --> 00:28:03,310
We all know it's him. It makes perfect sense.

638
00:28:03,310 --> 00:28:04,630
He's dating Anna,

639
00:28:04,630 --> 00:28:06,890
she's complaining about not getting child support,

640
00:28:06,890 --> 00:28:07,590
she gets fed up,

641
00:28:07,590 --> 00:28:10,260
she tells Miguel where the dope money's stashed at St. Angela's.

642
00:28:10,260 --> 00:28:11,310
Yeah, and he grabs a gun and a mask.

643
00:28:11,310 --> 00:28:13,290
He sets out to commit the easiest robbery of his life.

644
00:28:13,290 --> 00:28:13,900
Exactly.

645
00:28:13,910 --> 00:28:16,560
Hey, good news. After we ID'd Miguel,

646
00:28:16,560 --> 00:28:18,490
we pulled video of his last known address.

647
00:28:18,490 --> 00:28:19,580
Good.

648
00:28:20,900 --> 00:28:22,490
That's Miguel entering his house

649
00:28:22,490 --> 00:28:24,580
45 minutes after the robbery and shooting.

650
00:28:24,580 --> 00:28:25,800
Same pants and shoes,

651
00:28:25,800 --> 00:28:27,690
and he's carrying the same bag we saw in the other video.

652
00:28:27,690 --> 00:28:29,640
So let's get a warrant. Scoop his ass up.

653
00:28:29,640 --> 00:28:30,720
Right.

654
00:28:37,340 --> 00:28:38,540
I've got up top.

655
00:28:42,930 --> 00:28:43,480
Did you hear him?

656
00:28:43,480 --> 00:28:45,030
Announce your office and hit that door.

657
00:28:45,030 --> 00:28:46,100
Be ready.

658
00:28:57,180 --> 00:28:58,290
Upstairs window.

659
00:28:59,090 --> 00:29:00,170
We just got made.

660
00:29:01,990 --> 00:29:03,110
Chicago PD!

661
00:29:03,900 --> 00:29:05,040
Hey, put your hands on the table.

662
00:29:05,040 --> 00:29:05,790
Hands on the table.

663
00:29:05,790 --> 00:29:07,940
Ma'am, walk towards me. Walk towards me.

664
00:29:07,940 --> 00:29:08,800
Keep your hands where I can see them.

665
00:29:08,800 --> 00:29:10,400
Sit down. Put your hands on the table.

666
00:29:10,400 --> 00:29:12,100
- Hands on the table. - Come on.

667
00:29:12,100 --> 00:29:13,360
I got you. Go.

668
00:29:16,240 --> 00:29:17,510
All right, it's all right.

669
00:29:17,510 --> 00:29:19,200
Stop, put your hands on your head and walk towards me.

670
00:29:19,210 --> 00:29:21,190
- Ruz, I got a runner! - Go, go, go, go, go, go, go!

671
00:29:25,930 --> 00:29:27,070
It's over, Miguel.

672
00:29:27,120 --> 00:29:28,290
Get your hands up.

673
00:29:29,380 --> 00:29:30,440
Now.

674
00:29:36,540 --> 00:29:37,240
Be smart, man.

675
00:29:37,240 --> 00:29:38,400
Put your hands up nice and high.

676
00:29:38,400 --> 00:29:39,940
Don't make this hard on yourself.

677
00:29:40,210 --> 00:29:41,390
You wanna die?

678
00:29:44,730 --> 00:29:46,400
'Cause I won't ask again.

679
00:29:53,330 --> 00:29:54,570
Hands behind your back.

680
00:29:57,330 --> 00:29:58,400
Here we go.

681
00:29:58,870 --> 00:30:01,070
We got about 50K in here, maybe more.

682
00:30:01,070 --> 00:30:02,300
Best part is,

683
00:30:02,960 --> 00:30:05,270
Miguel left it in the church collection bag.

684
00:30:05,410 --> 00:30:07,300
The St. Angela's logo on it and everything.

685
00:30:07,300 --> 00:30:08,030
Nice.

686
00:30:08,030 --> 00:30:09,410
Book it into evidence, will you?

687
00:30:09,410 --> 00:30:10,520
Copy that.

688
00:30:11,700 --> 00:30:14,410
You talked to Kev about all this Doyle business?

689
00:30:14,590 --> 00:30:16,450
A little. You?

690
00:30:16,450 --> 00:30:18,160
I'm trying. He's shutting me out.

691
00:30:18,800 --> 00:30:20,310
He's having a hard time, boss.

692
00:30:20,320 --> 00:30:22,290
These guys, they're playing too rough.

693
00:30:22,420 --> 00:30:23,970
They're just getting started.

694
00:30:25,320 --> 00:30:26,770
He did what he had to do.

695
00:30:27,040 --> 00:30:28,920
It's different for him. It just is.

696
00:30:29,110 --> 00:30:31,720
You know, being a Black cop here in Chicago these days.

697
00:30:32,320 --> 00:30:33,730
Can't be easy.

698
00:30:40,090 --> 00:30:41,180
Go on in.

699
00:30:46,030 --> 00:30:47,060
Ma'am.

700
00:30:48,400 --> 00:30:49,540
We got a problem.

701
00:30:49,980 --> 00:30:51,940
Kay, I don't know what you're talking about.

702
00:30:54,630 --> 00:30:57,550
I just watched the bodycam footage of Miguel Cortez's arrest.

703
00:30:57,550 --> 00:31:00,310
You kicked down the damn door without announcing your office.

704
00:31:00,310 --> 00:31:01,670
That's because we got made.

705
00:31:01,670 --> 00:31:03,580
I just spoke to the state's attorney's office.

706
00:31:03,580 --> 00:31:06,040
They've determined the entry improper,

707
00:31:06,040 --> 00:31:08,510
so all the evidence recovered is inadmissible.

708
00:31:08,510 --> 00:31:10,010
Okay, look, I get it.

709
00:31:10,020 --> 00:31:12,440
Nobody wants to hand out no-knocks these days.

710
00:31:13,350 --> 00:31:15,480
We had a warrant to enter the premises

711
00:31:15,480 --> 00:31:16,650
and apprehend the offender.

712
00:31:16,650 --> 00:31:17,980
You're not hearing me.

713
00:31:18,650 --> 00:31:20,400
You entered the premises

714
00:31:20,400 --> 00:31:23,010
without announcing your office.

715
00:31:23,010 --> 00:31:25,210
There were women and children in there.

716
00:31:25,210 --> 00:31:27,010
It could've gone bad a hundred different ways.

717
00:31:27,010 --> 00:31:28,380
But it didn't.

718
00:31:29,620 --> 00:31:30,950
Like I said before, Sergeant,

719
00:31:30,950 --> 00:31:33,370
I want you to succeed more than you know.

720
00:31:34,980 --> 00:31:37,360
But the days of playing God are over.

721
00:31:40,220 --> 00:31:42,320
The quicker you understand that, the better.

722
00:31:49,640 --> 00:31:51,940
Right or wrong, there's nothing we can do.

723
00:31:52,010 --> 00:31:53,900
All the evidence has been tossed.

724
00:31:53,910 --> 00:31:55,680
You guys, I'm sorry. I saw the blinds move.

725
00:31:55,680 --> 00:31:56,280
I don't know what I was supposed to do.

726
00:31:56,280 --> 00:31:58,350
Adam, no, listen to me, you did the right thing.

727
00:31:58,350 --> 00:32:00,760
What I'm trying to tell you is, it doesn't matter.

728
00:32:00,760 --> 00:32:01,780
You get it?

729
00:32:01,780 --> 00:32:03,240
The reality is,

730
00:32:03,690 --> 00:32:06,210
no one's got the guts to stand up for police right now.

731
00:32:06,210 --> 00:32:09,000
Not the mayor, not the white shirts in the ivory tower.

732
00:32:09,000 --> 00:32:10,010
No one.

733
00:32:11,310 --> 00:32:12,600
Get used to it.

734
00:32:15,510 --> 00:32:16,740
Okay, so...

735
00:32:17,340 --> 00:32:19,240
the only real evidence we have now

736
00:32:19,690 --> 00:32:21,420
is that video of Miguel entering his house

737
00:32:21,420 --> 00:32:22,280
carrying the bag.

738
00:32:22,280 --> 00:32:24,390
Same bag he was carrying when he tried to shoot the priest.

739
00:32:24,390 --> 00:32:26,980
Yeah, I get it, but try proving it's the same bag.

740
00:32:26,980 --> 00:32:28,800
I mean, a black bag is a black bag.

741
00:32:29,610 --> 00:32:31,940
We gotta start all over from the beginning,

742
00:32:31,940 --> 00:32:33,520
build a whole new case.

743
00:32:34,730 --> 00:32:36,260
So find more surveillance video,

744
00:32:36,270 --> 00:32:37,780
new witnesses.

745
00:32:38,810 --> 00:32:40,590
Meantime, I'm gonna talk to Miguel.

746
00:32:40,590 --> 00:32:43,270
I can still let him know how much evidence we have.

747
00:32:45,050 --> 00:32:46,500
For God's sakes, bro,

748
00:32:46,890 --> 00:32:49,390
the collection bags are marked St. Angela's.

749
00:32:50,330 --> 00:32:52,250
It doesn't get any better than that.

750
00:32:58,500 --> 00:33:00,050
I don't know what you're talking about.

751
00:33:04,880 --> 00:33:07,110
Your girlfriend told you about the money

752
00:33:07,750 --> 00:33:10,550
because Carlos stopped providing for their daughter,

753
00:33:11,200 --> 00:33:12,040
and honestly?

754
00:33:12,040 --> 00:33:13,800
I don't even blame her.

755
00:33:15,230 --> 00:33:17,120
I mean, that guy makes a lot of money selling dope.

756
00:33:17,120 --> 00:33:19,010
Least he can do is break off a few grand

757
00:33:19,010 --> 00:33:20,700
every month for his little girl.

758
00:33:21,600 --> 00:33:23,550
I told you. I didn't do it.

759
00:33:23,550 --> 00:33:25,720
You stole the money, you ran out,

760
00:33:25,720 --> 00:33:27,600
the priest chased after you,

761
00:33:27,750 --> 00:33:29,390
he tried to tackle you,

762
00:33:30,240 --> 00:33:31,950
so you opened fire.

763
00:33:32,440 --> 00:33:33,830
That's what happened.

764
00:33:34,620 --> 00:33:36,860
You know, the fact that you were so close

765
00:33:36,870 --> 00:33:38,210
and you missed,

766
00:33:38,900 --> 00:33:41,510
that tells me you probably just trying to scare the guy.

767
00:33:44,400 --> 00:33:46,320
But see, the problem is, Miguel,

768
00:33:47,150 --> 00:33:49,620
the reason we're all so upset

769
00:33:50,740 --> 00:33:53,340
is one of your bullets hit a 5-year-old girl.

770
00:33:55,220 --> 00:33:58,110
She's fighting for her life right now at Chicago Med.

771
00:33:59,130 --> 00:34:02,050
Chicago is a-- it's a dangerous place.

772
00:34:15,380 --> 00:34:17,650
You confess to the robbery

773
00:34:18,120 --> 00:34:19,330
and the shooting,

774
00:34:21,730 --> 00:34:23,190
you can cut yourself a deal.

775
00:34:23,190 --> 00:34:24,040
You understand?

776
00:34:24,040 --> 00:34:25,950
But you wait, play the long game,

777
00:34:27,110 --> 00:34:29,350
you try and take this thing to trial,

778
00:34:30,450 --> 00:34:33,710
state's attorney is gonna nail your ass to a cross.

779
00:34:35,440 --> 00:34:37,920
- I want my lawyer. - What is the matter with you?

780
00:34:37,920 --> 00:34:39,470
Yo, I'm done talking!

781
00:34:52,940 --> 00:34:54,480
Heard what happened with the search.

782
00:34:54,480 --> 00:34:56,610
- Yeah, well, it is what it is. - New world.

783
00:34:56,610 --> 00:34:59,050
Everybody's paying attention to the fine print all of a sudden.

784
00:34:59,050 --> 00:35:00,810
- Where is he? - In there.

785
00:35:04,570 --> 00:35:06,930
Mr. Diaz, what can I do for you?

786
00:35:08,110 --> 00:35:11,160
You tell me you caught the person who killed my little girl.

787
00:35:13,570 --> 00:35:14,370
You're saying...

788
00:35:14,370 --> 00:35:15,760
She died an hour ago.

789
00:35:16,490 --> 00:35:17,880
Oh, my God.

790
00:35:18,850 --> 00:35:22,040
I'm--I'm so sorry.

791
00:35:22,420 --> 00:35:23,550
Did you arrest the killer?

792
00:35:24,650 --> 00:35:26,220
We're still working on that,

793
00:35:27,120 --> 00:35:28,540
but the good news is,

794
00:35:29,390 --> 00:35:30,440
we know who did it.

795
00:35:30,440 --> 00:35:33,000
We just need a little more evidence, build a better case.

796
00:35:33,000 --> 00:35:34,850
If you know who did it, isn't that enough?

797
00:35:35,400 --> 00:35:38,100
Doesn't that mean you already have a good case?

798
00:35:38,980 --> 00:35:40,800
Sometimes the law is complicated.

799
00:35:40,800 --> 00:35:42,560
No, it's simple.

800
00:35:43,130 --> 00:35:44,590
It is real simple.

801
00:35:45,350 --> 00:35:47,300
So who killed her? Who killed her?

802
00:35:47,300 --> 00:35:48,420
- Who is he? - I can't tell you that.

803
00:35:48,420 --> 00:35:49,330
Who is he? Where is he?

804
00:35:49,330 --> 00:35:50,990
If you don't take care of this, I will!

805
00:35:51,000 --> 00:35:52,140
Sir, please!

806
00:35:52,140 --> 00:35:54,100
No. My little girl is dead.

807
00:35:54,830 --> 00:35:56,780
And I want that son of a bitch who killed her to go down,

808
00:35:56,780 --> 00:35:58,770
- to pay for what he did! - So do I.

809
00:35:59,380 --> 00:36:02,800
And I promise you I will do everything I can.

810
00:36:03,080 --> 00:36:04,620
But it's, it's just...

811
00:36:24,440 --> 00:36:26,760
Grab Miguel and put him in a cage.

812
00:36:27,350 --> 00:36:29,500
Boss, you sure that's a good idea?

813
00:36:33,220 --> 00:36:35,400
- Excuse me? - Sarge, I mean...

814
00:36:35,550 --> 00:36:36,520
come on, things are different now.

815
00:36:36,520 --> 00:36:37,360
I'll do what you need me to do--

816
00:36:37,360 --> 00:36:39,120
Laura Diaz just died.

817
00:36:40,250 --> 00:36:41,700
Five years old.

818
00:36:43,500 --> 00:36:46,070
The prick who pulled the trigger's sitting right in there.

819
00:36:46,190 --> 00:36:47,290
Doesn't matter.

820
00:36:49,380 --> 00:36:52,630
Of course it matters. He killed her.

821
00:36:52,630 --> 00:36:54,180
I know he did, we all know he did,

822
00:36:54,180 --> 00:36:56,200
but we can't just drag his ass down to a cage.

